   "trap": "- Sit **forward** (not back); pinch the **soft cartilaginous part (alae)**, not the bony bridge\n- Hold **continuously for at least 10–15 min** (Australian sources: RCH ~10 min, RACGP/AFP up to 15–20 min) before reassessing\n- Only escalate to **chemical cautery (silver nitrate)** to a SINGLE visible anterior bleeding point if direct pressure fails AND the point is seen\n- **NEVER cauterise both sides** of the septum at the same visit (septal perforation risk)\n- If cautery fails or bleeding is diffuse/posterior: place **anterior pack** (Rapid Rhino / nasal tampon)\n- **Posterior bleed** (bleeding down the throat despite anterior pack, often elderly/hypertensive/anticoagulated) = admit, **posterior pack/balloon, ENT**",
