   "whatFirst": "- **Otoscopy** to exclude wax/effusion/perforation\n- **Tuning-fork tests (Weber/Rinne)** to confirm sensorineural pattern\n- Then **urgent ENT referral** for audiogram and consideration of high-dose corticosteroids",
   "discriminator": "- Sensorineural: Weber lateralises to **GOOD ear**, Rinne positive (AC>BC bilaterally), **normal otoscopy** = emergency; steroids\n- Conductive: Weber to **BAD ear**, Rinne negative on affected side, wax/effusion visible = treat the cause, not an emergency\n- Unilateral SSNHL: mandates **MRI to exclude vestibular schwannoma**/retrocochlear pathology",
